# gen171 (dynamic knowledge): on a definitional gap, parrot0 reads a local
# markdown source into RAM through the in-C learner and says honestly that it just
# learned it. If the topic has no local markdown source, it says so without a
# queue or external Python handoff.
> tell me about prime number
< I didn't know about prime number, so I just read it up: natural number greater than 1 that is not a product of two smaller natural numbers.
> tell me about quaternions
< I don't actually know about quaternions yet, and I have no source to read on it.
